The paper deals with parallel algorithms for graph problems, specifically the maximum matching problem. This suggests that it could belong to categories related to distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), or graph theory (cs.GT). The focus on parallel computation and the use of frameworks like MapReduce and Hadoop further supports the likelihood of cs.DC and cs.DS.
